1
00:00:00,213 --> 00:00:02,527
It’s so early, and we already
have so many customers!

2
00:00:02,552 --> 00:00:03,826
- Are you serious?
- Yes, look!

3
00:00:04,228 --> 00:00:05,228
I’ll place this here, okay?

4
00:00:08,114 --> 00:00:09,188
Here you go, enjoy!

5
00:00:09,532 --> 00:00:11,139
Thank you! Enjoy.

6
00:00:11,164 --> 00:00:12,164
Oh, excuse me.

7
00:00:12,455 --> 00:00:13,675
Orb, look at this.

8
00:00:14,032 --> 00:00:15,325
Yes, what is it?

9
00:00:15,416 --> 00:00:16,416
Look at this.

10
00:00:16,669 --> 00:00:17,669
Here, right?

11
00:00:19,009 --> 00:00:20,493
- It looks just like them!
- Isn’t it cute?!

12
00:00:20,518 --> 00:00:21,518
- Really?
- It’s definitely them.

13
00:00:21,543 --> 00:00:22,863
- It has to be them!
- You think so?

14
00:00:23,140 --> 00:00:24,524
- Yes.
- What about this, huh?

15
00:00:24,628 --> 00:00:25,628
This one?

16
00:00:25,778 --> 00:00:26,778
This one, this one?

17
00:00:27,384 --> 00:00:30,923
Oh, that’s cute!
So cute! Look!

18
00:00:30,948 --> 00:00:32,121
It was taken last time!

19
00:00:34,831 --> 00:00:35,831
Kuya!

20
00:00:36,202 --> 00:00:37,615
Kuya, what’s this?

21
00:00:38,206 --> 00:00:39,206
Oh, that’s mine!

22
00:00:40,547 --> 00:00:41,547
Thank you!

23
00:00:41,936 --> 00:00:42,936
Perfect.

24
00:00:43,344 --> 00:00:44,364
Ate, I’ll just take a picture.

25
00:00:44,389 --> 00:00:45,756
Ah, okay. Okay.

26
00:00:46,570 --> 00:00:47,570
Deliver?

27
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:50,420
Hey!

28
00:00:51,227 --> 00:00:52,420
If you’re taking a
picture,

29
00:00:52,444 --> 00:00:54,182
it should just be the product
and the owner—

30
00:00:54,207 --> 00:00:55,207
why are you in it too?!

31
00:00:55,232 --> 00:00:56,516
It’s just company policy.

32
00:00:56,541 --> 00:00:58,136
- Ah, is that policy? Sorry.
- Thank you!

33
00:00:58,293 --> 00:01:00,040
Thank you, sorry about that.

34
00:01:00,319 --> 00:01:02,213
Uncle Iskineport!

35
00:01:05,005 --> 00:01:06,005
What is it, Tash?

36
00:01:06,030 --> 00:01:09,163
Tash, what did you
order this time?

37
00:01:09,188 --> 00:01:13,262
I bought something for display here
in the bake shop.

38
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:15,552
- Ahh.
- Ahh, okay, okay.

39
00:01:15,577 --> 00:01:16,582
What is it?

40
00:01:17,693 --> 00:01:19,593
A display. Here it is.

41
00:01:20,290 --> 00:01:21,290
Oh, oh.

42
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:23,138
- Huh? A t-shirt?
- A t-shirt?

43
00:01:23,163 --> 00:01:25,024
- T-shirt?
- You’re going to display this, Tash?

44
00:01:25,049 --> 00:01:26,049
Huh?

45
00:01:26,648 --> 00:01:28,228
This isn’t what I ordered!

46
00:01:29,385 --> 00:01:30,458
What am I going to do with this?

47
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:32,494
It doesn’t even fit me.

48
00:01:33,586 --> 00:01:35,806
If none of you want it…

49
00:01:39,275 --> 00:01:41,515
I love this color of t-shirt.
I’ll just take it!

50
00:01:41,630 --> 00:01:42,893
Try it on, Iskineport!

51
00:01:43,412 --> 00:01:44,412
- Huh?
- Oh?

52
00:01:44,423 --> 00:01:46,069
I’ll take it! I’ll take
it, let me try it on.

53
00:01:46,094 --> 00:01:47,659
- Okay, try it on.
- Here, here...

54
00:01:47,684 --> 00:01:49,845
Go ahead, you all handle things here
while I try this on.

55
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:52,147
Iskineport, the blue t-shirt…

56
00:01:52,179 --> 00:01:54,857
Good thing I worked out earlier;
I’ve got abs now.

57
00:01:55,273 --> 00:01:56,466
- Abs?
- Totally ripped.

58
00:02:00,196 --> 00:02:01,196
Wow!

59
00:02:01,273 --> 00:02:02,406
- Wow!
- Look how it fits perfectly!

60
00:02:03,086 --> 00:02:04,493
Just right!

61
00:02:04,518 --> 00:02:05,853
- Honestly, it looks like a cropped top!
- It looks good on you!

62
00:02:05,878 --> 00:02:06,878
Does it fit?

63
00:02:06,883 --> 00:02:08,954
- It’s super loose, man!
- Really?

64
00:02:08,979 --> 00:02:11,440
Why do I look like
a suman from Antipolo?

65
00:02:11,519 --> 00:02:13,633
It just needs sugar.

66
00:02:13,658 --> 00:02:15,976
I thought it was loose?!

67
00:02:16,185 --> 00:02:18,778
No, no!
To make it fit, leave it to me!

68
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:21,126
- You’ve got this, huh?
- I’ll fix it up for you.

69
00:02:21,825 --> 00:02:23,025
I’ll wear this to JS Prom.

70
00:02:23,489 --> 00:02:26,184
You know, we should complain
to that seller.

71
00:02:28,574 --> 00:02:29,574
- But—
- Oh...

72
00:02:30,592 --> 00:02:31,592
- Why?
- Ah, Tash...

73
00:02:31,614 --> 00:02:32,727
This wasn’t for you.

74
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,530
It says Atasha Perez on it!

75
00:02:35,555 --> 00:02:36,555
Oh yeah, you’re right!

76
00:02:36,748 --> 00:02:39,911
The address is correct,
but the name is wrong.

77
00:02:40,235 --> 00:02:42,541
Oh my god, you’re right.

78
00:02:42,694 --> 00:02:48,161
One wrong piece of information
can lead to a one big disaster.

79
00:02:49,681 --> 00:02:50,681
So crazy!

80
00:02:50,895 --> 00:02:52,688
- Does it fit?
- Yeah, here it is!

81
00:02:53,176 --> 00:02:55,922
It fits now?
Why does it look so loose again?

82
00:02:57,357 --> 00:02:59,077
My back hurts, though.

83
00:02:59,102 --> 00:03:00,252
- Why?
- Why?

84
00:03:01,069 --> 00:03:02,069
Can you check?

85
00:03:02,955 --> 00:03:04,202
- Huh?
- Is it a wound?

86
00:03:05,306 --> 00:03:06,433
- Huh? None.
- None!

87
00:03:06,547 --> 00:03:08,767
There’s nothing,
Uncle Iskineport, nothing.

88
00:03:09,011 --> 00:03:10,091
- Why does it sting?
- It’s just sweat!

89
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,104
It might be from scissors.
Scissors?

90
00:03:14,307 --> 00:03:16,460
Wait, wait! Ow! Iskineport!

91
00:03:16,485 --> 00:03:17,815
He cut my back!

92
00:03:18,048 --> 00:03:22,381
Iskineport! I didn’t mean to scratch you!
Sorry, Iskineport!

93
00:03:23,129 --> 00:03:24,515
I got carried away! Ow!

94
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,033
Thank you, Kuya.

95
00:04:31,464 --> 00:04:32,944
I’ll leave this here for now.

96
00:04:33,457 --> 00:04:33,870
I’ll take care of it.

97
00:04:34,801 --> 00:04:35,915
Tash, are you okay?

98
00:04:36,702 --> 00:04:39,749
You look tired, like
you’re not feeling well.

99
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:43,390
My whole body hurts, and
my head too, Tito Iskineport.

100
00:04:43,894 --> 00:04:45,674
It’s because you’ve been doing so much.

101
00:04:45,742 --> 00:04:49,728
But we need to finish this order
for the grand reopening, right?

102
00:04:49,915 --> 00:04:50,915
That’s true.

103
00:04:53,822 --> 00:04:54,822
It’s so heavy.

104
00:04:55,639 --> 00:04:57,310
- Hey, Tash!
- Hey, how are you guys?

105
00:04:57,335 --> 00:04:59,290
- Kuya Iskineport.
- Hey, let us help you.

106
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,414
- Are you okay?
- Let us help you.

107
00:05:01,555 --> 00:05:04,315
It’s better if I rest for a while.

108
00:05:04,786 --> 00:05:05,786
Are you okay?

109
00:05:06,612 --> 00:05:08,998
- Hey.
- Oh my god, wait a second.

110
00:05:09,044 --> 00:05:10,238
- Hey, Tash!
- Hey!

111
00:05:10,453 --> 00:05:12,446
- She’s collapsing, she’s collapsing!
- What’s happening to you?!

112
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:13,923
- You’re not feeling well!
- Hey, hey, hey!

113
00:05:14,929 --> 00:05:18,508
Hey, hey, Tash, Tash, Tash!
Oh my god, oh my god! Tash, Tash, Tash!

114
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:22,280
Let’s finish this,
stop pushing yourself.

115
00:05:22,305 --> 00:05:24,613
Wait. Hey! You’re burning up!

116
00:05:24,943 --> 00:05:26,630
You’re spinning, you’re about to fall—

117
00:05:26,655 --> 00:05:27,968
- Tito, take her home!
- You’re burning up, Tash!

118
00:05:28,007 --> 00:05:29,911
- Take her home, Uncle.
- I’ll take her home!

119
00:05:29,936 --> 00:05:30,936
I’ll take her home!

120
00:05:31,217 --> 00:05:33,010
- Home? We’re already at home!
- To the clinic! Why home?!

121
00:05:33,288 --> 00:05:35,041
Why the clinic? At home!

122
00:05:35,066 --> 00:05:37,103
- To the clinic!
- At home! I said.

123
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:40,075
- To the clinic.
- Guys, stop this. Stop it! Stop it!

124
00:05:40,659 --> 00:05:44,819
I don’t need the clinic,
I’m fine, okay?

125
00:05:45,692 --> 00:05:46,692
Okay?

126
00:05:46,717 --> 00:05:47,717
Are you okay?

127
00:05:49,472 --> 00:05:50,472
Hey, hey!

128
00:05:53,992 --> 00:05:55,859
I’m fine.

129
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:01,660
Why is this happening?

130
00:06:01,746 --> 00:06:03,606
It’s like Tash is possessed!

131
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:07,132
Oh, oh, oh!

132
00:06:08,392 --> 00:06:12,352
To all our Kapatid, the number of
active MPox cases has risen again.

133
00:06:13,657 --> 00:06:18,305
We encourage everyone to always wash
their hands, avoid skin-to-skin contact,

134
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:20,579
and be alert for symptoms such as fever,

135
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:25,306
headaches, body pain,
dizziness, rashes, or blisters.

136
00:06:25,965 --> 00:06:28,425
Oh no, this is dangerous!

137
00:06:28,489 --> 00:06:31,929
It might become like
the pandemic again!

138
00:06:32,015 --> 00:06:34,528
- I hope not.
- Oh no, let’s hope not, Grandma Maxi.

139
00:06:34,553 --> 00:06:36,856
That’s what they say;
it’s spreading.

140
00:06:36,881 --> 00:06:39,062
It’s scary, right?

141
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,584
Don’t be scared.
I’ll take care of you, Chacha!

142
00:06:41,775 --> 00:06:43,379
- Don’t be scared.
- BFF! BFF!

143
00:06:44,387 --> 00:06:45,940
You just walk in suddenly.

144
00:06:46,057 --> 00:06:47,104
Don’t you have a home?

145
00:06:47,129 --> 00:06:48,129
Yes.

146
00:06:48,136 --> 00:06:49,281
- Sit down.
- Sorry about that.

147
00:06:49,306 --> 00:06:50,425
Take a seat.

148
00:06:51,156 --> 00:06:52,156
Oh.

149
00:06:52,341 --> 00:06:53,621
Why are you speaking like that?

150
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:54,833
Should I charge you rent?

151
00:06:55,237 --> 00:06:56,237
Well…

152
00:06:56,262 --> 00:06:59,243
You’re so busy watching that
you didn’t notice I came in,

153
00:07:00,088 --> 00:07:01,088
huh?

154
00:07:01,113 --> 00:07:02,367
What’s happening now?

155
00:07:02,773 --> 00:07:03,773
Oh, nothing.

156
00:07:03,868 --> 00:07:05,674
I just wanted to
introduce someone to you.

157
00:07:05,699 --> 00:07:06,699
- Who?!
- Who?!

158
00:07:09,895 --> 00:07:10,895
Come in.

159
00:07:11,259 --> 00:07:13,003
- Here he is.
- It’s me, it’s me.

160
00:07:13,254 --> 00:07:14,254
My cousin.

161
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:16,267
A doctor.

162
00:07:16,653 --> 00:07:17,713
Dr. Dennis.

163
00:07:18,023 --> 00:07:20,227
- Here, these are my friends.
- Hi, Aga, Aga.

164
00:07:20,305 --> 00:07:21,305
Hello, hello.

165
00:07:21,684 --> 00:07:23,067
- Chacha.	Chacha
- Hi!

166
00:07:23,092 --> 00:07:24,353
- Maxi.
- That’s Grandma Maxi.

167
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:27,150
This is the Da Pers family.

168
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,270
The Pers family.

169
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:31,242
As in Pers,
because “first” is me.

170
00:07:31,562 --> 00:07:32,562
It was taken from me.

171
00:07:32,697 --> 00:07:33,957
There you go again.

172
00:07:34,365 --> 00:07:35,959
Haven’t you moved on yet?

173
00:07:37,602 --> 00:07:40,955
Doc, you look familiar to me?

174
00:07:41,272 --> 00:07:42,472
Ah, ah, ah…

175
00:07:42,558 --> 00:07:44,992
that’s because I’m a doctor-vlogger.

176
00:07:45,184 --> 00:07:47,051
Maybe you’ve seen me on social media?

177
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,907
Maybe, huh?

178
00:07:49,932 --> 00:07:52,751
No, no, because my cousin here
is a doctor, right?

179
00:07:53,115 --> 00:07:55,742
He’s looking for a clinic
in this area.

180
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:59,141
I thought, since you might not
really be able to pay for the bakery,

181
00:07:59,204 --> 00:08:02,491
we could turn your bakery
into his clinic.

182
00:08:02,516 --> 00:08:03,516
If you want.

183
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:04,530
Please don’t.

184
00:08:04,637 --> 00:08:06,683
Don’t. There you go again, oh!

185
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,800
Don’t do that.

186
00:08:08,524 --> 00:08:09,791
You’re always like this—

187
00:08:09,945 --> 00:08:11,292
Kuya! Kuya, Kuya!

188
00:08:11,327 --> 00:08:12,408
- Oh, what?!
- Something happened to Tash!

189
00:08:12,667 --> 00:08:13,774
What happened?!

190
00:08:13,799 --> 00:08:15,074
Oh, oh! What happened?!

191
00:08:15,207 --> 00:08:16,593
Why are you dragging her?!

192
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:17,733
What happened?!

193
00:08:19,101 --> 00:08:20,242
What happened?!

194
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:21,720
Here, here! Put her here!

195
00:08:21,745 --> 00:08:24,423
Don’t neglect my granddaughter!

196
00:08:24,448 --> 00:08:26,560
Iskineport, put her here, quickly!

197
00:08:26,811 --> 00:08:27,851
Help me!

198
00:08:28,099 --> 00:08:29,526
Put her here!

199
00:08:30,658 --> 00:08:31,867
Gently! Gently!

200
00:08:31,892 --> 00:08:34,718
Don’t neglect my granddaughter!

201
00:08:35,169 --> 00:08:36,504
- There!
- Oh my god!

202
00:08:36,529 --> 00:08:38,898
We dragged her all the way
from Quezon City,

203
00:08:39,058 --> 00:08:41,098
went to Taguig, and now
we’re just dragging her around.

204
00:08:41,123 --> 00:08:42,431
Why are you dragging her?!

205
00:08:42,456 --> 00:08:43,871
No, Andres was
saying something earlier!

206
00:08:43,896 --> 00:08:46,601
Dad, she was saying her body
and head hurt earlier.

207
00:08:46,877 --> 00:08:48,720
- Huh?!
- Then she got the hots!

208
00:08:48,831 --> 00:08:49,831
She's got the hots?!

209
00:08:50,741 --> 00:08:52,308
What do you mean
she's got the hots?

210
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,139
- She’s burning up.
- Ah, she has a fever!

211
00:08:54,177 --> 00:08:56,133
My head’s burning up
because of you!

212
00:08:56,177 --> 00:08:58,284
Wait. Doc! Perfect timing, Doc!

213
00:08:58,646 --> 00:09:00,466
Look at her, please!

214
00:09:00,491 --> 00:09:02,141
- Do your best, Doc!
- Of course, of course!

215
00:09:02,378 --> 00:09:03,962
- Of course, of course!
- Look at her, please!

216
00:09:07,174 --> 00:09:08,174
Wait, okay.

217
00:09:08,249 --> 00:09:09,249
What could it be?

218
00:09:10,329 --> 00:09:11,542
Oh no!

219
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,630
What is it, Doc?!

220
00:09:13,675 --> 00:09:14,675
- Why?!
- Wait a second!

221
00:09:15,301 --> 00:09:16,301
Nobody move!

222
00:09:16,749 --> 00:09:18,676
Don’t make a sound!

223
00:09:19,036 --> 00:09:20,036
Nobody breathe!

224
00:09:20,417 --> 00:09:22,149
Nobody talk!
Nobody leave!

225
00:09:22,929 --> 00:09:23,929
It's positive.

226
00:09:23,954 --> 00:09:26,054
- Positive?! For what?!
- Positive.

227
00:09:26,922 --> 00:09:28,635
MPox is now
in the Da Pers family.

228
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:29,855
MPox?!

229
00:09:30,402 --> 00:09:31,742
Do I have MPox?!

230
00:09:40,149 --> 00:09:41,729
Ugh! Disinfect!

231
00:09:41,991 --> 00:09:43,978
Germs, viruses!

232
00:09:44,257 --> 00:09:46,044
You, you, disinfect properly, okay?

233
00:09:46,366 --> 00:09:47,871
It’s necessary, oh no!

234
00:09:48,065 --> 00:09:50,006
- Mmm, Tolits, that’s P500, okay?
- Yes.

235
00:09:50,031 --> 00:09:52,724
But when the ayuda comes,
you owe me P1,000, alright?

236
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:55,927
What, Tso K?!

237
00:09:56,098 --> 00:09:58,719
That’s crazy!
P500 and you want P1,000 back?

238
00:09:58,744 --> 00:10:00,449
- Yes!
- That’s not 5-6 anymore,

239
00:10:00,473 --> 00:10:02,845
that’ s 5-10,
and your height’s only 5’4”!

240
00:10:03,496 --> 00:10:05,862
Don’t you feel sorry for
this poor squid ball vendor?

241
00:10:06,317 --> 00:10:06,997
Okay, fine!

242
00:10:07,022 --> 00:10:08,022
- You’re unbelievable.
- Fine, fine!

243
00:10:08,186 --> 00:10:09,399
I’ll just go home.

244
00:10:09,539 --> 00:10:10,951
Forget it.
Never mind.

245
00:10:11,014 --> 00:10:12,771
- Hey, hey, don’t be like that, Tso K.
- And why not?

246
00:10:12,796 --> 00:10:14,819
When the ayuda comes,
we’ll pay you back, okay?

247
00:10:15,073 --> 00:10:16,093
That’s the thing!

248
00:10:16,372 --> 00:10:17,838
I’m just trying to help!

249
00:10:17,863 --> 00:10:19,589
I’m just advancing my help

250
00:10:19,614 --> 00:10:24,008
because I know the ayuda will come
to our barangay because of MPox.

251
00:10:24,212 --> 00:10:26,662
Why are you complaining?

252
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,040
This is just help!

253
00:10:28,327 --> 00:10:29,327
Can you believe it?

254
00:10:29,432 --> 00:10:31,266
MPox has reached
Barangay Singko.

255
00:10:31,689 --> 00:10:35,076
And of all people,
Kuya Aga got it!

256
00:10:35,595 --> 00:10:36,882
What do you mean,
“of all people”?!

257
00:10:37,417 --> 00:10:39,777
This is all Aga’s fault!

258
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,620
He’s always the unlucky one
in this barangay!

259
00:10:43,328 --> 00:10:45,615
But isn’t Tash the one
who tested positive?

260
00:10:45,808 --> 00:10:47,221
Why are you so mad at Kuya Aga?

261
00:10:47,414 --> 00:10:50,337
It’s Tash, sure,
but who’s the head of the family?

262
00:10:50,854 --> 00:10:51,854
Kuya Aga!

263
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:53,997
- Who makes the decisions?
- Kuya Aga!

264
00:10:54,022 --> 00:10:56,052
- Who’s in charge?
- Kuya Aga!

265
00:10:56,077 --> 00:10:57,989
See? It’s Aga!

266
00:10:58,014 --> 00:10:59,674
That’s it. So it’s Aga’s fault!

267
00:10:59,699 --> 00:11:01,594
So it’s Aga’s fault!

268
00:11:01,734 --> 00:11:04,601
He’s the one bringing
bad luck to this barangay!

269
00:11:04,749 --> 00:11:07,092
So until next time, see you around.

270
00:11:07,152 --> 00:11:10,460
I’m Doc Dennis.
Like, share, and subscribe!

271
00:11:10,687 --> 00:11:12,142
- Hold on a second.
- Bye-bye!

272
00:11:12,174 --> 00:11:14,010
- Doc Dennis!
- Hey, how’s it going?

273
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:19,123
Oh, I just wanted to thank you
for diagnosing everything so quickly.

274
00:11:19,148 --> 00:11:20,535
If you hadn’t,
we could have been infected!

275
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:22,029
- Oh, that?
- Yeah.

276
00:11:22,054 --> 00:11:25,451
No problem! Of course,
I’m fast with these things!

277
00:11:25,576 --> 00:11:26,763
Don’t block me there.

278
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:28,500
I’m really quick
with these things, right?

279
00:11:28,572 --> 00:11:31,759
Just a quick look,
and I already know what the solution is.

280
00:11:31,784 --> 00:11:32,784
My gosh!

281
00:11:33,918 --> 00:11:35,984
Is this protection enough?

282
00:11:36,159 --> 00:11:37,693
Am I safe now?!

283
00:11:37,814 --> 00:11:40,300
Oh, see that?
Look at that?

284
00:11:40,518 --> 00:11:42,252
That needs an executive check-up!

285
00:11:42,354 --> 00:11:43,980
Good thing I’m a doctor!
I’m a doctor!

286
00:11:44,005 --> 00:11:45,005
- You’re a doctor, yeah.
- I’m a doctor!

287
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:46,181
- Yes.
- I’m a doctor!

288
00:11:46,254 --> 00:11:48,361
I’ll be the one to check
you up later, okay?

289
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,701
Hey, hey!

290
00:11:49,726 --> 00:11:51,758
Did you hear that?!
Did you hear that?!

291
00:11:51,783 --> 00:11:52,987
My check-up is free!

292
00:11:53,068 --> 00:11:55,948
Tso K, my check-up is free!

293
00:11:57,001 --> 00:11:59,531
- Stop it! Stop it already!
- Tso K, my free—

294
00:11:59,556 --> 00:12:00,674
...check-up!

295
00:12:01,409 --> 00:12:02,709
Oh my god, you’re amazing, Doc!

296
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:06,429
- Stop it, you’re making me itch!
- I miss you!

297
00:12:06,454 --> 00:12:07,536
You’re like MPox!

298
00:12:07,673 --> 00:12:09,393
Doc, I think I need a check-up too.

299
00:12:09,462 --> 00:12:10,966
Ah, you want a check-up?

300
00:12:10,991 --> 00:12:13,432
- Yes, a check-up.
- Okay, line up again outside.

301
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,525
Stop it!

302
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:21,454
Back in my day,

303
00:12:21,478 --> 00:12:25,302
just using a washcloth
could bring a fever down.

304
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:26,796
Do you put it on the forehead?

305
00:12:27,536 --> 00:12:28,536
Mm-hmm.

306
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:31,790
Oh dear!

307
00:12:33,927 --> 00:12:35,149
- Huh?
- Here we go!

308
00:12:35,174 --> 00:12:36,174
Here we go!

309
00:12:36,199 --> 00:12:37,199
- Tash!
- Tash!

310
00:12:37,224 --> 00:12:38,793
- What’s happening?
- Wake up!

311
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:41,973
Atasha, my child,
we’re taking you to the doctor.

312
00:12:42,172 --> 00:12:43,779
Yeah, Dad called a taxi.

313
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:46,468
Come on, Tash, just rest for now.

314
00:12:47,539 --> 00:12:48,788
What happened?

315
00:12:49,303 --> 00:12:51,691
Tash, you fainted.

316
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:53,806
And you felt hot.

317
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,574
That’s why Grandma Maxi
was taking care of you.

318
00:12:58,286 --> 00:13:01,934
That’s why my head and body hurt.

319
00:13:01,959 --> 00:13:04,166
- My head and body hurt.
- Because, Atasha,

320
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:06,620
you’re overworking yourself.

321
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:10,213
That’s why you got sick.

322
00:13:10,603 --> 00:13:14,714
Maybe she’s just tired from Eat Bulaga,
doing it every day.

323
00:13:15,555 --> 00:13:16,900
Oh no, and it’s not just any illness!

324
00:13:17,719 --> 00:13:19,027
It’s MPox!

325
00:13:19,052 --> 00:13:20,052
Huh?!

326
00:13:20,077 --> 00:13:21,796
- MPox?
- I have MPox?!

327
00:13:21,948 --> 00:13:24,170
No, you don't!
No, you don't!

328
00:13:24,195 --> 00:13:26,678
You’re scaring the child
with all this MPox talk!

329
00:13:27,156 --> 00:13:28,514
Maybe you’re the one
who infected her;

330
00:13:28,538 --> 00:13:29,865
you’re the only one
who looks like a monkey here!

331
00:13:32,477 --> 00:13:34,799
Oh wait,
here’s the taxi you booked.

332
00:13:35,184 --> 00:13:36,429
- It’s here!
- Okay!

333
00:13:36,531 --> 00:13:39,309
- It’s close now.
- Don’t worry, okay?

334
00:13:39,646 --> 00:13:40,646
Relax.

335
00:13:43,146 --> 00:13:44,146
Why?

336
00:13:44,241 --> 00:13:45,618
- It’s red.
- Is that a rash?!

337
00:13:45,705 --> 00:13:46,808
A rash?!

338
00:13:47,013 --> 00:13:48,758
There’s a lot, Kuya,
here on the right.

339
00:13:49,979 --> 00:13:51,651
- It is a rash!
- It’s a rash!

340
00:13:53,539 --> 00:13:54,745
- What do we do?!
- What is this?!

341
00:13:55,408 --> 00:13:56,656
It wasn’t here earlier!

342
00:13:56,681 --> 00:13:59,125
MPox this, MPox that,
you’ve been saying MPox all along!

343
00:13:59,831 --> 00:14:01,640
- What’s that?! What are you doing?!
- There, you saw it, guys.

344
00:14:01,665 --> 00:14:03,019
Oh no, my plants will die there!

345
00:14:03,044 --> 00:14:06,419
We’re here, guys,
at the ground zero of MPox.

346
00:14:06,444 --> 00:14:07,625
There they are. Look!

347
00:14:07,791 --> 00:14:10,494
Hey, what’s this ground zero
nonsense you’re saying?!

348
00:14:10,658 --> 00:14:15,165
Move aside, we need to use the path
to take someone to the service!

349
00:14:15,639 --> 00:14:17,966
Grandma Maxi, what service?

350
00:14:18,011 --> 00:14:21,217
I already sent the vehicle
Aga called home.

351
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:23,056
You can’t go out!

352
00:14:23,108 --> 00:14:24,703
You need to be disinfected!

353
00:14:25,434 --> 00:14:26,725
Stop it already!

354
00:14:27,133 --> 00:14:28,473
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

355
00:14:28,503 --> 00:14:30,374
And who are you,
what are you doing here?!

356
00:14:30,914 --> 00:14:32,289
Wait, what’s this?!
What’s going on?! Wait, hey!

357
00:14:32,841 --> 00:14:33,980
What’s all this commotion?!

358
00:14:34,005 --> 00:14:36,097
- What’s happening here?!
- Wait, wait, you can’t go out!

359
00:14:36,121 --> 00:14:39,397
You’ll spread the MPox!

360
00:14:39,422 --> 00:14:41,100
- What MPox?!
- No one has MPox!

361
00:14:41,125 --> 00:14:42,703
- MPox!
- How would the virus spread?!

362
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:48,717
For MPox to spread, there needs
to be direct skin-to-skin contact.

363
00:14:48,954 --> 00:14:50,506
It’s not airborne!

364
00:14:50,559 --> 00:14:55,001
Well, still, BFF!
It’s contagious!

365
00:14:55,438 --> 00:14:56,802
Yeah, yeah!

366
00:14:57,701 --> 00:14:58,701
Wait, wait!

367
00:14:58,826 --> 00:15:01,359
Don’t jump to conclusions!

368
00:15:01,384 --> 00:15:05,320
Atasha hasn’t even
tested positive for MPox!

369
00:15:05,345 --> 00:15:06,597
- Right!
- Chacha,

370
00:15:06,783 --> 00:15:09,155
- What?!
- Please understand us!

371
00:15:09,482 --> 00:15:11,943
We’re taking care of you,
aren’t we? Right, kids?!

372
00:15:11,968 --> 00:15:13,687
Yes! Right, right!

373
00:15:13,965 --> 00:15:20,357
Atasha feels dizzy,
she’s unwell, tired from work.

374
00:15:20,382 --> 00:15:22,110
- Right!
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

375
00:15:22,224 --> 00:15:25,585
You keep talking.
Who’s the doctor here, you or me?

376
00:15:25,806 --> 00:15:26,806
Who is it? Me, right?!

377
00:15:26,866 --> 00:15:28,834
Right!
I’m the doctor here!

378
00:15:29,229 --> 00:15:32,356
So if I were you,
I’d just stay inside. Otherwise—

379
00:15:32,609 --> 00:15:35,106
Otherwise, what? Go on. Otherwise, what?

380
00:15:35,526 --> 00:15:36,526
Quarantine!

381
00:15:36,573 --> 00:15:38,106
Quarantine!

382
00:15:38,258 --> 00:15:39,810
Quarantine!

383
00:15:39,893 --> 00:15:41,305
Quarantine!

384
00:15:41,547 --> 00:15:43,068
- Quarantine!
- What’s happening here?!

385
00:15:43,093 --> 00:15:44,747
Quarantine!

386
00:15:45,119 --> 00:15:46,362
Quarantine!

387
00:15:46,422 --> 00:15:48,162
Wait, wait, let’s go inside,
let’s go inside!

388
00:15:48,193 --> 00:15:49,441
Grandma Maxi! Grandma Maxi!

389
00:15:50,266 --> 00:15:51,775
Quarantine!

390
00:15:51,906 --> 00:15:53,336
Quarantine!

391
00:15:53,684 --> 00:15:54,896
Quarantine!

392
00:15:54,993 --> 00:15:55,993
Quarantine!

393
00:15:56,018 --> 00:15:57,018
Grabe kayo!
You’re unbelievable!

394
00:15:57,043 --> 00:15:58,222
Quarantine!

395
00:15:59,339 --> 00:16:00,339
Quarantine!

396
00:16:00,370 --> 00:16:01,533
Just don’t go out!

397
00:16:08,546 --> 00:16:09,630
Grandma, what are you doing?

398
00:16:09,655 --> 00:16:11,219
- What’s happening?
- What’s going on?

399
00:16:11,244 --> 00:16:13,231
Yeah, Grandma.
Are you making rice cakes?

400
00:16:13,326 --> 00:16:14,987
You turned Tash into one!

401
00:16:15,084 --> 00:16:17,417
This is how we do it
in my province!

402
00:16:17,474 --> 00:16:21,189
We do this to get rid of all illnesses!

403
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,725
You even have guava leaves for washing!

404
00:16:25,643 --> 00:16:28,043
Guys, relax.

405
00:16:28,508 --> 00:16:29,987
I’m still here.

406
00:16:30,058 --> 00:16:33,166
Grandma’s just treating me.
Thank you!

407
00:16:33,191 --> 00:16:34,191
It’s effective!

408
00:16:34,347 --> 00:16:36,868
Why does she sound like
she’s being exorcised?

409
00:16:40,225 --> 00:16:43,140
Yeah, we thought something
happened to you, Tash!

410
00:16:43,716 --> 00:16:46,726
Wait a second, but Grandma,
is this really effective?

411
00:16:47,232 --> 00:16:51,341
It’s already 2024, Grandma.
Do you still believe in leaves and herbs?

412
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:52,693
What’s wrong with you?

413
00:16:53,069 --> 00:16:56,018
Back in my day,
we didn’t have medicine.

414
00:16:56,106 --> 00:16:59,973
We only used herbal remedies
for applying and drinking!

415
00:17:01,286 --> 00:17:04,347
You know,
I really doubt that Dennis.

416
00:17:05,086 --> 00:17:06,545
- Why?
- The way he moves,

417
00:17:06,569 --> 00:17:07,911
he doesn’t seem like a doctor.

418
00:17:09,121 --> 00:17:10,539
- That’s how I feel!
- Yeah, right.

419
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:13,857
- Oh my god!
- What’s that?!

420
00:17:23,519 --> 00:17:26,010
We’re here live in Barangay Singko

421
00:17:26,148 --> 00:17:29,288
where a family has reportedly
tested positive for MPox.

422
00:17:29,571 --> 00:17:32,862
Joining us is Dr. Dennis,
the doctor who diagnosed them.

423
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:35,606
- Doc?
- Ah, it’s confirmed.

424
00:17:36,123 --> 00:17:38,705
They need to stay quarantined,

425
00:17:38,818 --> 00:17:40,788
and of course, as the doctor here,

426
00:17:40,991 --> 00:17:45,984
it’s my job to check on all the residents
to prevent the virus fromspreading.

427
00:17:46,708 --> 00:17:50,676
But don’t forget to like, share,
and subscribe to my page, okay?

428
00:17:52,893 --> 00:17:58,408
Oh, the Pers family may look clean,
but they’re dirty!

429
00:17:58,639 --> 00:17:59,639
Filthy!

430
00:17:59,844 --> 00:18:02,013
Tensions are high here, folks.

431
00:18:02,351 --> 00:18:04,357
Let’s ask the residents for their opinion.

432
00:18:05,204 --> 00:18:09,065
Do you think the Pers family should be
removed from Barangay Cinco?

433
00:18:09,154 --> 00:18:10,263
Yes, definitely!

434
00:18:10,334 --> 00:18:11,334
Wait, wait, wait!

435
00:18:12,148 --> 00:18:13,148
Why remove the family?

436
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:17,203
Just kick Aga out of the barangay,
not the whole family.

437
00:18:17,461 --> 00:18:18,461
Tso K!

438
00:18:18,486 --> 00:18:19,486
Tso K!

439
00:18:19,591 --> 00:18:20,591
Tso K!

440
00:18:22,297 --> 00:18:23,764
- Tso K!
- Spickerspine!

441
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:24,867
Come here for a second!

442
00:18:24,893 --> 00:18:28,243
Hold on, hold on!
You just came out from inside!

443
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:30,019
Uncle K, help us.

444
00:18:30,128 --> 00:18:32,389
We don’t want to stay in
Kuya’s house anymore!

445
00:18:34,302 --> 00:18:35,649
- Hey, stop that. Why—
- Tso K!

446
00:18:35,674 --> 00:18:36,674
Spickerspine!

447
00:18:37,628 --> 00:18:39,537
It’s Iskineport, not Spickerspine!

448
00:18:39,562 --> 00:18:41,354
Oh, I got it wrong, it’s Iskineport!

449
00:18:41,669 --> 00:18:43,214
Stop it, you’re making me itch.

450
00:18:43,239 --> 00:18:44,239
Don’t come near me!

451
00:18:44,264 --> 00:18:46,932
Don’t worry,
I’ve got my elbow mask on.

452
00:18:47,052 --> 00:18:48,546
I just waved at them, anyway.

453
00:18:48,571 --> 00:18:50,495
And I just listened to Tash.

454
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:52,570
My eardrums are totally safe!

455
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:54,425
Stop it! Go back over there!

456
00:18:54,450 --> 00:18:56,352
- Tso K!
- Enough already!

457
00:18:58,546 --> 00:18:59,716
Finally!

458
00:19:00,470 --> 00:19:01,724
I’m going to succeed!

459
00:19:02,686 --> 00:19:06,202
Aga will definitely leave
this barangay now.

460
00:19:07,822 --> 00:19:09,653
You’re amazing, cousin!
You’re amazing!

461
00:19:10,251 --> 00:19:14,245
Imagine diagnosing
MPox right away!

462
00:19:14,882 --> 00:19:16,797
That? Cousin, it’s nothing!

463
00:19:17,155 --> 00:19:18,155
Just for the views!

464
00:19:19,490 --> 00:19:20,605
What? For the views?!

465
00:19:20,828 --> 00:19:23,306
Ah, ah… for the news!

466
00:19:23,331 --> 00:19:25,961
News! Awareness, cousin!
Awareness.

467
00:19:25,985 --> 00:19:28,489
So people here will know
what MPox is, right?

468
00:19:28,871 --> 00:19:30,125
They need to know that!

469
00:19:30,817 --> 00:19:32,111
But you, cousin,

470
00:19:32,135 --> 00:19:35,257
why are you so eager
to get Aga out of here?

471
00:19:35,914 --> 00:19:42,320
Ah, well, I thought
their MPox wasn’t real.

472
00:19:42,432 --> 00:19:43,432
Oh.

473
00:19:44,382 --> 00:19:46,049
- Really?
- Nothing, just saying.

474
00:19:46,774 --> 00:19:48,641
I’ve been thinking,
don’t you have a clinic?

475
00:19:48,878 --> 00:19:49,878
Clinic?

476
00:19:49,957 --> 00:19:51,320
Ah… yeah, I used to.

477
00:19:51,345 --> 00:19:52,345
Ah… yeah,

478
00:19:52,349 --> 00:19:56,599
but I’m looking for a new location,
one with more people, like here!

479
00:19:56,967 --> 00:19:59,319
Look at all these people!
It’s perfect.

480
00:19:59,719 --> 00:20:00,719
That’s great!

481
00:20:00,889 --> 00:20:02,131
Don’t worry, cousin!

482
00:20:02,228 --> 00:20:03,828
I’ll take care of it!

483
00:20:03,853 --> 00:20:06,089
That’s what I like about you, cousin!
That’s what I like about you, cousin!

484
00:20:09,179 --> 00:20:10,179
Cousin,

485
00:20:10,688 --> 00:20:12,368
I’ve noticed you’ve been
scratching yourself.

486
00:20:12,392 --> 00:20:13,616
What’s that?

487
00:20:14,149 --> 00:20:17,379
I don’t know.
It just started itching suddenly.

488
00:20:17,647 --> 00:20:19,022
Looks like MPox, cousin!

489
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:20,580
That’s MPox!

490
00:20:20,605 --> 00:20:21,605
Hey, no!

491
00:20:21,865 --> 00:20:23,108
How could it be MPox?

492
00:20:24,254 --> 00:20:25,684
Maybe it’s just a bite?

493
00:20:25,922 --> 00:20:26,922
Cousin,

494
00:20:27,122 --> 00:20:30,453
could it be that when those two
from Aga’s place hugged you earlier,

495
00:20:30,477 --> 00:20:31,477
you caught it?

496
00:20:31,585 --> 00:20:32,585
- Hey!
- Wait,

497
00:20:32,610 --> 00:20:33,954
maybe they need
to know about this!

498
00:20:34,079 --> 00:20:36,354
Wait… wait,
don’t jump to conclusions!

499
00:20:36,379 --> 00:20:37,589
Why are you in such a hurry?!

500
00:20:37,613 --> 00:20:38,613
Hold on!

501
00:20:38,638 --> 00:20:40,138
They need to know this!

502
00:20:40,163 --> 00:20:42,405
No, maybe…
maybe it’s nothing.

503
00:20:43,425 --> 00:20:45,982
It feels like it’s fading, anyway!

504
00:20:46,007 --> 00:20:47,007
It’ll fade!

505
00:20:47,032 --> 00:20:48,362
It seems to fade!

506
00:20:48,387 --> 00:20:51,211
You don’t need to go to the hospital;
I’m a doctor, cousin, right?

507
00:20:51,236 --> 00:20:52,843
- See?
- I’m a doctor, right?

508
00:20:52,909 --> 00:20:53,909
I’ll take care of it.

509
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:55,844
You’re amazing.
You’re really a doctor!

510
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,094
I’ll handle it.
Let’s keep this a secret, cousin, okay?!

511
00:20:58,119 --> 00:20:59,119
Of course!

512
00:20:59,477 --> 00:21:00,477
Your hands are so quick.

513
00:21:02,212 --> 00:21:03,212
Okay, fine.

514
00:21:09,431 --> 00:21:10,431
Anne!

515
00:21:11,006 --> 00:21:12,951
Don’t you have food
at home, at Tso K’s?

516
00:21:13,697 --> 00:21:14,769
Oh, it’s not that.

517
00:21:14,913 --> 00:21:16,210
We have food.
It’s just that this is my favorite.

518
00:21:16,711 --> 00:21:18,232
Oh! It’s okay that you’re here,
I don’t mind.

519
00:21:18,257 --> 00:21:20,055
It’s just that I’ve noticed you’re always
around. Right, right? It's Orbs, yeah?

520
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,431
Not that I’m complaining!

521
00:21:23,734 --> 00:21:24,734
Right, right?

522
00:21:25,096 --> 00:21:26,096
It's Orbs!

523
00:21:26,126 --> 00:21:27,126
Orb!

524
00:21:27,151 --> 00:21:28,700
Dad, this is my best friend.

525
00:21:29,309 --> 00:21:30,909
- That’s why she’s here.
- And here we are.

526
00:21:31,143 --> 00:21:32,143
- Yep, here we are!
- Hey!

527
00:21:33,307 --> 00:21:34,816
Hey, Tasha!

528
00:21:35,817 --> 00:21:38,324
Tasha! How are you?

529
00:21:38,349 --> 00:21:39,349
Yes!

530
00:21:39,374 --> 00:21:40,950
I’m feeling a lot better.

531
00:21:41,282 --> 00:21:44,221
Super, super thank you, guys,
for everything and for your concern.

532
00:21:44,246 --> 00:21:45,246
Thank you, guys!

533
00:21:45,271 --> 00:21:50,422
Of course, in good times and bad,
your family is here—your Pers family.

534
00:21:50,447 --> 00:21:52,453
That’s right!
That’s the Pers family.

535
00:21:52,588 --> 00:21:54,564
No, I mean, it’s fine now.

536
00:21:54,744 --> 00:21:56,489
You don’t need
to hug me, though!

537
00:21:57,374 --> 00:21:58,374
We love you!

538
00:21:58,938 --> 00:22:00,726
- Just relax, okay?
- Wait!

539
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,371
How are your rashes?

540
00:22:04,095 --> 00:22:07,107
They’re still there,
but they’re fading.

541
00:22:07,580 --> 00:22:10,955
Tash, maybe you got them
from your clothes earlier.

542
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:15,881
Isn’t your clothesline near
that tree with hairy caterpillars?

543
00:22:16,329 --> 00:22:20,044
Oh yeah, maybe the leaves
with those caterpillars caused it.

544
00:22:20,105 --> 00:22:23,369
And that can make you
feel unwell, right?

545
00:22:23,814 --> 00:22:25,499
Not really. I feel better now.

546
00:22:26,451 --> 00:22:30,728
That’s good, my apo,
and thank goodness you don’t have MPox.

547
00:22:30,775 --> 00:22:31,963
That’s right, Lola Maxi!

548
00:22:31,988 --> 00:22:35,637
So it’s good that we had
Iskineport and Chard here.

549
00:22:36,441 --> 00:22:42,315
I even called my doctor friend
to rule out that MPox thing!

550
00:22:42,538 --> 00:22:47,247
Whatever happens, even if you have rashes,
we’re here for you.

551
00:22:47,369 --> 00:22:49,488
We’ll never leave you.

552
00:22:50,539 --> 00:22:51,885
Aww, thank you, guys!

553
00:22:52,004 --> 00:22:53,004
Okay, let’s eat!

554
00:22:54,772 --> 00:22:56,215
- Wait, do you want to eat?
- You want to eat?

555
00:22:57,711 --> 00:22:58,344
Wait!

556
00:22:58,427 --> 00:22:59,427
- Eat!
- Oh, eat!

557
00:23:00,492 --> 00:23:01,492
Eat!

558
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:04,567
Delicious!

559
00:23:06,517 --> 00:23:09,051
That’s right!
That’s good for your health!

560
00:23:09,952 --> 00:23:11,334
Why are all of you here?

561
00:23:11,399 --> 00:23:12,805
You know, Tash,

562
00:23:13,938 --> 00:23:20,140
if MPox from outside comes in here,
we’ll get MPox before you do.

563
00:23:20,165 --> 00:23:21,177
Mmm-hmm! That’s right!

564
00:23:21,202 --> 00:23:22,693
We can handle it all here!

565
00:23:23,135 --> 00:23:24,135
Me too.

566
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:25,329
It’s because we love you.

567
00:23:28,593 --> 00:23:30,084
- You love me?
- Hmmm?

568
00:23:32,890 --> 00:23:35,533
No! Well, uh, maybe, maybe.

569
00:23:35,573 --> 00:23:36,573
Hmmm?

570
00:23:37,612 --> 00:23:39,442
Oh, you’re so happy!

571
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:42,521
But seriously,
that’s how it is, right?

572
00:23:42,789 --> 00:23:45,867
Even before we admit it,
we already care for each other.

573
00:23:46,019 --> 00:23:48,231
That’s the Pers family!

574
00:23:48,256 --> 00:23:49,470
Yes!

575
00:23:49,495 --> 00:23:51,191
- Aww...
- Yes, Tash!

576
00:23:51,377 --> 00:23:53,232
Thanks, guys! Okay...

577
00:23:56,412 --> 00:23:57,176
- Hold on.
- Why?

578
00:23:57,201 --> 00:23:58,201
Just stay here.

579
00:24:01,136 --> 00:24:03,233
Where is it?
It’s taking so long!

580
00:24:03,771 --> 00:24:04,941
Are you sure it’s here?

581
00:24:04,966 --> 00:24:08,250
This area seems sketchy.
You know this place is dangerous!

582
00:24:08,378 --> 00:24:09,378
You’re always saying it’s dangerous!

583
00:24:09,403 --> 00:24:14,570
This is where Kuya Aga said to wait
for his doctor friend. Dr. Mendoza!

584
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:15,964
Ah, Dr. Mendoza?

585
00:24:16,381 --> 00:24:17,799
- I wonder what she look like?
- I think she’ll pass by here.

586
00:24:18,399 --> 00:24:19,399
Dr. Mendoza?

587
00:24:19,424 --> 00:24:20,787
- That corner,
- Yeah?

588
00:24:21,436 --> 00:24:23,242
I know this area well.

589
00:24:23,541 --> 00:24:25,123
- If you turn left there, then—
- Excuse me?

590
00:24:26,083 --> 00:24:29,572
- There, my group is—
- Don’t interrupt!

591
00:24:29,815 --> 00:24:32,554
We’ve been waiting here forever,
and I’m about to smack you!

592
00:24:33,122 --> 00:24:34,122
Rude!

593
00:24:34,987 --> 00:24:35,987
There, if—

594
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:37,123
- Hello?
- At the corner...

595
00:24:37,148 --> 00:24:40,508
One more word and
I’ll punch your pancreas.

596
00:24:41,319 --> 00:24:42,319
It's right around here.

597
00:24:42,974 --> 00:24:43,986
Mestiza!

598
00:24:44,053 --> 00:24:45,247
Oh no, don’t believe her!

599
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:47,750
I told you this place is dangerous!

600
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:50,478
She might be part of a scam!

601
00:24:51,516 --> 00:24:55,221
Miss, sorry,
but we don’t have money right now.

602
00:24:55,595 --> 00:24:59,129
If you really want to find customers,
you should be out at night.

603
00:24:59,721 --> 00:25:02,576
Or during the day,
people are usually at work.

604
00:25:02,843 --> 00:25:03,843
And we’re not like that, you know.

605
00:25:03,868 --> 00:25:06,098
Wait, wait, wait, hold on.

606
00:25:06,165 --> 00:25:07,613
You’re looking for someone, right?

607
00:25:08,346 --> 00:25:09,421
- Yes!
- You’re waiting for someone?

608
00:25:09,446 --> 00:25:11,798
Oh, our brother’s friend.

609
00:25:11,823 --> 00:25:13,390
- Who?
- Dr. Mendoza.

610
00:25:13,415 --> 00:25:14,473
That’s me.

611
00:25:14,523 --> 00:25:15,523
Hmm?

612
00:25:16,487 --> 00:25:17,835
- That’s me!
- Really?!

613
00:25:18,072 --> 00:25:19,072
I don’t know.

614
00:25:19,097 --> 00:25:20,585
Oh no! No way.

615
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:25,124
Our Kuya Aga doesn’t make friends
with someone beautiful and sexy like you.

616
00:25:25,149 --> 00:25:25,610
That’s right!

617
00:25:25,711 --> 00:25:27,268
- He avoids those types!
- All his friends are like that.

618
00:25:27,346 --> 00:25:31,746
If anyone loves sexy people like you,
it’s Director Danica Paras!

619
00:25:33,005 --> 00:25:34,021
- True!
- That type!

620
00:25:34,349 --> 00:25:35,349
Wait, wait!

621
00:25:36,004 --> 00:25:40,277
Aren’t you the one who came
with Aga to my check-up last time?

622
00:25:41,053 --> 00:25:42,878
- Oh? You know each other?
- The one with the—?

623
00:25:42,924 --> 00:25:45,452
Oh, yeah, you’re Dr. Mendoza.

624
00:25:45,477 --> 00:25:46,477
We’ve been waiting for you.

625
00:25:46,611 --> 00:25:47,611
Good thing you arrived!

626
00:25:48,402 --> 00:25:49,716
- Perfect timing!
- Welcome!

627
00:25:49,741 --> 00:25:51,085
Let’s go see Kuya Aga.

628
00:25:51,259 --> 00:25:53,452
- Don’t continue talking about what I had.
- This is embarrassing!

629
00:25:53,477 --> 00:25:55,614
- Fine, fine. Come on, let’s go!
- Let’s go over there.

630
00:25:55,639 --> 00:25:57,081
You’re all so silly, what’s wrong with you?

631
00:25:57,283 --> 00:25:58,610
You’re embarrassing!

632
00:25:58,647 --> 00:25:59,806
Stop making noise!

633
00:26:00,565 --> 00:26:01,565
Okay.

634
00:26:02,595 --> 00:26:03,801
You need P300.

635
00:26:05,056 --> 00:26:06,224
- Here.
- That’s perfect.

636
00:26:06,711 --> 00:26:08,717
You’ll owe me P3,000
when the ayuda arrives.

637
00:26:09,018 --> 00:26:10,018
P3,000?

638
00:26:10,043 --> 00:26:11,324
It’s better if we understand each other.

639
00:26:11,349 --> 00:26:13,678
Ah, ah. You have tuberculosis!

640
00:26:14,181 --> 00:26:17,962
Take this twice a day, okay?

641
00:26:18,519 --> 00:26:19,549
How much is this, Doc?

642
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:21,567
Oh, it’s super cheap!
One thousand five hundred!

643
00:26:21,988 --> 00:26:23,236
That includes my
check-up fee, okay?

644
00:26:23,744 --> 00:26:25,071
One tablet is P1,500?!

645
00:26:25,503 --> 00:26:27,276
- Okay.
- Thank you, thank you!

646
00:26:27,866 --> 00:26:29,829
Come back to me, okay?

647
00:26:29,894 --> 00:26:30,894
You’ll owe me P1,000 in return.

648
00:26:31,692 --> 00:26:32,692
Cousin,

649
00:26:34,173 --> 00:26:35,173
thanks so much.

650
00:26:35,650 --> 00:26:37,141
This is perfect.

651
00:26:37,295 --> 00:26:39,592
They borrow from you and
then come to me for a check-up—

652
00:26:39,619 --> 00:26:41,322
we both profit from this, cousin!

653
00:26:43,393 --> 00:26:44,526
Your idea is genius, huh?

654
00:26:44,946 --> 00:26:46,159
I told you, didn’t I?

655
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,684
Leave it to me!

656
00:26:50,426 --> 00:26:51,583
- But, wait—
- You know,

657
00:26:51,607 --> 00:26:54,808
I really don’t trust the
face of that Doc Dennis.

658
00:26:55,186 --> 00:26:58,449
Add Uncle K to the mix,
and it’s double trouble!

659
00:26:58,653 --> 00:27:00,310
- True!
- But you know,

660
00:27:00,334 --> 00:27:03,436
Doc Dennis’ face looks familiar.

661
00:27:03,943 --> 00:27:06,513
I feel like I’ve seen him
on social media.

662
00:27:06,538 --> 00:27:07,909
- Hold on, let me check.
- Yeah, right.

663
00:27:07,934 --> 00:27:09,691
I feel like I’ve seen him too.

664
00:27:10,513 --> 00:27:11,513
Let’s search it.

665
00:27:11,538 --> 00:27:15,023
There it is! Look,
Doc Dennis is an actor!

666
00:27:15,064 --> 00:27:18,007
- Huh?! Let me see!
- Oh, oh! Right?!

667
00:27:18,654 --> 00:27:21,369
You’re so dumb, aren’t you?!

668
00:27:21,672 --> 00:27:22,672
So dumb!

669
00:27:22,752 --> 00:27:23,818
Read the caption next time!

670
00:27:24,293 --> 00:27:25,669
Read next time!

671
00:27:26,253 --> 00:27:29,047
Oh no, Kuya Aga
needs to know about this.

672
00:27:29,072 --> 00:27:30,072
P2,000.

673
00:27:30,097 --> 00:27:31,097
Mmm!

674
00:27:38,744 --> 00:27:40,301
Your throat is clear.

675
00:27:40,861 --> 00:27:42,825
Let me take a look at those rashes.

676
00:27:48,693 --> 00:27:50,432
It’s just an allergic reaction.

677
00:27:50,529 --> 00:27:51,529
Huh?!

678
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:55,418
I’ll just give you a cream
to apply twice a day.

679
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:57,837
Wait, wait, Doc. That’s it?!

680
00:27:58,413 --> 00:27:59,413
Yes.

681
00:27:59,668 --> 00:28:01,843
It’s not MPox?

682
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:05,026
Ah, MPox is a different case.

683
00:28:05,216 --> 00:28:10,836
It’s a viral and infectious disease
with symptoms like painful rashes,

684
00:28:11,229 --> 00:28:12,229
fever,

685
00:28:12,486 --> 00:28:14,522
headaches,

686
00:28:14,731 --> 00:28:17,670
- body aches, and weakness.
- Mm-hmm?

687
00:28:17,864 --> 00:28:23,804
You can get it from close contact

688
00:28:23,881 --> 00:28:26,075
like skin-to-skin,

689
00:28:26,548 --> 00:28:27,766
mouth-to-skin,

690
00:28:27,860 --> 00:28:31,773
or mouth-to-mouth with a
person or animal that has MPox.

691
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:34,211
However,

692
00:28:34,236 --> 00:28:36,333
MPox is still a threat right now.

693
00:28:36,358 --> 00:28:37,891
Let’s stay cautious.

694
00:28:38,309 --> 00:28:47,051
But don’t be scared—it’s not a new disease,
and there are vaccines available for it.

695
00:28:47,405 --> 00:28:53,371
So, Doctor, you’re confirming that
this isn’t MPox?

696
00:28:53,652 --> 00:28:59,444
It could also be microbes or a virus
caused by changing climates.

697
00:28:59,991 --> 00:29:05,912
It’s best to stay updated
with health news.

698
00:29:05,937 --> 00:29:06,937
Yes.

699
00:29:07,001 --> 00:29:11,220
So we’ll know what new
illnesses are emerging.

700
00:29:11,245 --> 00:29:12,344
Yes, Doc.

701
00:29:12,685 --> 00:29:15,976
So, does this mean
we can go out now?

702
00:29:16,023 --> 00:29:18,072
Yes, you may go out!

703
00:29:18,097 --> 00:29:19,097
Oh, yay!

704
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:25,719
That’s what I was saying!

705
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:28,855
You know, Doctor,
I called you because

706
00:29:29,193 --> 00:29:31,417
this Doctor Dennis

707
00:29:31,987 --> 00:29:35,430
claimed it was MPox
without even running a test!

708
00:29:35,719 --> 00:29:36,725
Wait a second.

709
00:29:37,305 --> 00:29:38,389
Doc Dennis?

710
00:29:38,414 --> 00:29:40,024
- Dennis, yes! Dennis!
- Yes, yes.

711
00:29:40,154 --> 00:29:43,469
Is he the one with
the mole below his lip?

712
00:29:43,558 --> 00:29:44,242
- That’s him!
- That’s him!

713
00:29:44,267 --> 00:29:45,896
- Yeah, the one with a mustache!
- That's him!

714
00:29:45,921 --> 00:29:46,940
That's him!

715
00:29:46,983 --> 00:29:49,369
- Oh, no.
- Why?

716
00:29:49,406 --> 00:29:50,535
- Kuya Aga!
- Hey!

717
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:53,700
Kuya Aga! Oh no,
Kuya Aga, look!

718
00:29:53,806 --> 00:29:55,679
Look! That Doctor Dennis is a fraud!

719
00:29:55,938 --> 00:29:57,035
He’s been reported to Tulfo!

720
00:29:57,132 --> 00:29:58,839
- Look at this!
- Reported to Tulfo?!

721
00:29:59,736 --> 00:30:03,623
He didn’t even finish his degree,
so he doesn’t have a license.

722
00:30:03,918 --> 00:30:06,662
In short, he’s a fake doctor!

723
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:08,305
Fake doctor?!

724
00:30:08,330 --> 00:30:09,846
- Fake?!
- What?!

725
00:30:11,170 --> 00:30:12,297
Here, take this.

726
00:30:13,819 --> 00:30:14,819
Wampayb!

727
00:30:15,696 --> 00:30:17,975
- Alright.
- Take care, and come back, okay?

728
00:30:18,714 --> 00:30:19,714
Cousin!

729
00:30:22,791 --> 00:30:23,791
Impressive, huh?

730
00:30:24,571 --> 00:30:25,595
You handled a lot!

731
00:30:27,645 --> 00:30:29,815
We’ve got a lot to split, cousin.

732
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:30,840
Yeah.

733
00:30:31,571 --> 00:30:32,571
Your idea is genius!

734
00:30:33,480 --> 00:30:34,480
Let’s keep it going—

735
00:30:34,981 --> 00:30:35,981
Ah!

736
00:30:36,006 --> 00:30:37,024
Perfect.

737
00:30:37,351 --> 00:30:38,526
- So much!
- Perfect.

738
00:30:38,551 --> 00:30:40,931
- There!
- Look, so much!

739
00:30:41,184 --> 00:30:43,939
Perfect! Perfect!

740
00:30:44,228 --> 00:30:45,798
What are you waiting for?
Arrest them!

741
00:30:45,958 --> 00:30:47,225
They’ve got MPox!

742
00:30:48,272 --> 00:30:49,272
Arrest them!

743
00:30:52,065 --> 00:30:53,186
Wait, why me? Why me?

744
00:30:53,853 --> 00:30:55,035
Why me? Why me?!

745
00:30:55,369 --> 00:30:57,751
There! There!

746
00:30:57,995 --> 00:30:59,989
No one here has MPox!

747
00:31:00,521 --> 00:31:02,642
You’re the real problem in this place!

748
00:31:02,667 --> 00:31:04,475
- That’s right!
- Right! Right!

749
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:05,950
You’re spreading false information!

750
00:31:06,417 --> 00:31:11,570
And we know you’re a
fake doctor without a license!

751
00:31:11,633 --> 00:31:12,773
Wait, wait, wait!

752
00:31:12,896 --> 00:31:13,896
Cousin, what’s this?!

753
00:31:14,022 --> 00:31:15,161
You’re not a doctor?!

754
00:31:15,186 --> 00:31:17,032
Cousin! What is this? Cousin!

755
00:31:17,685 --> 00:31:18,685
I am a doctor!

756
00:31:18,685 --> 00:31:20,273
I only need two more years to finish!

757
00:31:20,298 --> 00:31:22,402
- Oh, my goodness!
- That’s what I was saying!

758
00:31:25,705 --> 00:31:28,778
Wait, wait, let me explain!

759
00:31:29,260 --> 00:31:31,406
I didn’t know he wasn’t a doctor!

760
00:31:31,431 --> 00:31:33,295
I had nothing to do with this!

761
00:31:33,624 --> 00:31:36,782
That’s the problem with us.

762
00:31:37,011 --> 00:31:39,354
That’s the issue—
we spread false information,

763
00:31:39,378 --> 00:31:43,593
act like we know it all,
or rush into things!

764
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:46,853
There are so many people like this!

765
00:31:47,598 --> 00:31:48,834
Oh no, oh no, oh no!

766
00:31:48,867 --> 00:31:50,530
- That’s me!
- I agree!

767
00:31:50,555 --> 00:31:55,163
False news spreads faster than diseases!

768
00:31:55,188 --> 00:31:56,188
True!

769
00:31:56,213 --> 00:32:00,307
And thank goodness for the
strong support system of our family.

770
00:32:00,627 --> 00:32:01,627
True!

771
00:32:01,922 --> 00:32:04,134
Luckily, we got through it, right?

772
00:32:04,197 --> 00:32:05,670
Yay!

773
00:32:05,695 --> 00:32:08,721
You really are the model family here.

774
00:32:08,905 --> 00:32:13,579
When I start my own family,
I want it to be just like yours.

775
00:32:14,281 --> 00:32:15,808
Right!

776
00:32:15,859 --> 00:32:17,756
Cousin! I’m about to graduate, cousin!

777
00:32:17,781 --> 00:32:19,987
Unbelievable! You even lied to me!

778
00:32:20,314 --> 00:32:21,326
I thought you already graduated!

779
00:32:21,415 --> 00:32:23,746
- So, arrest me!
- Go ahead, take him away!

780
00:32:27,557 --> 00:32:28,703
Serves you right!

781
00:32:29,448 --> 00:32:30,448
Oh my goodness!

782
00:32:30,473 --> 00:32:31,746
At least he’s gone now!

783
00:32:31,771 --> 00:32:32,771
What a disgrace!

784
00:32:33,253 --> 00:32:34,349
I really didn’t know.

785
00:32:34,374 --> 00:32:36,225
Even I got tricked by my cousin.

786
00:32:36,530 --> 00:32:38,009
Why did it have to come to this?

787
00:32:38,092 --> 00:32:39,165
Everything got so chaotic!

788
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,001
Why are you scratching?

789
00:32:41,032 --> 00:32:42,110
Who… huh?

790
00:32:42,135 --> 00:32:44,127
- Why are you scratching?!
- Am I scratching?

791
00:32:44,152 --> 00:32:45,152
Why are you scratching?!

792
00:32:45,980 --> 00:32:46,980
Why are you scratching?!

793
00:32:47,887 --> 00:32:50,457
I don’t know!
Suddenly, I started itching!

794
00:32:55,733 --> 00:32:57,788
Hey! Hey!

795
00:32:58,939 --> 00:32:59,939
Hey!

796
00:33:00,234 --> 00:33:01,798
You left me behind!
What’s…?

797
00:33:03,283 --> 00:33:04,283
It’s so itchy!

798
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:09,350
Why didn’t you tell us you were
closing up so we could’ve helped?

799
00:33:09,415 --> 00:33:11,149
Dad, we’ve got this.

800
00:33:12,818 --> 00:33:14,060
My love, Andres…

801
00:33:14,155 --> 00:33:15,155
What?

802
00:33:21,237 --> 00:33:23,310
Hey! What’s this?!

803
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:24,583
What are you doing there?

804
00:33:24,846 --> 00:33:25,846
What’s with your face?

805
00:33:26,175 --> 00:33:28,412
What are you doing there?
Why are you smiling like that?!

806
00:33:28,685 --> 00:33:30,400
Don’t jump to conclusions!

807
00:33:30,713 --> 00:33:36,735
I’m smiling because
I’m so happy you’re my family.

808
00:33:39,450 --> 00:33:41,055
Well, thank you, Tash!

809
00:33:41,452 --> 00:33:42,973
You know, you’re really lucky.

810
00:33:43,204 --> 00:33:46,545
- Why?
- Because I’m handsome and kind.

811
00:33:48,019 --> 00:33:49,019
- Andres…
- Liar!

812
00:33:49,044 --> 00:33:52,824
Andres, you know what I dislike
most about this family? Bragging.

813
00:33:53,251 --> 00:33:55,088
We already know we’re handsome…

814
00:33:55,263 --> 00:33:58,140
- Huh?
- …and kind, and have amazing bodies.

815
00:33:58,668 --> 00:34:01,080
But I don’t like showing off.

816
00:34:01,763 --> 00:34:05,153
It’s ugly. Don’t do it!

817
00:34:05,184 --> 00:34:07,612
You two really are father and son!

818
00:34:08,605 --> 00:34:09,956
Amazing bodies, huh?!

819
00:34:12,047 --> 00:34:14,368
- Two weeks, just give me two weeks!
- Let’s see those abs!

820
00:34:14,407 --> 00:34:15,835
- Two weeks.
- No, wait.

821
00:34:15,859 --> 00:34:18,979
Seriously, I just want to say
from the bottom of my heart how

822
00:34:19,275 --> 00:34:22,578
proud we are of both of you.

823
00:34:23,974 --> 00:34:31,023
I mean, you decided to come back
here to help us, leaving behind your jobs.

824
00:34:31,127 --> 00:34:33,860
You didn’t have to do that.

825
00:34:33,885 --> 00:34:37,265
Of course, for us,
you should’ve prioritized yourselves.

826
00:34:37,528 --> 00:34:42,594
But you still did it—you left your jobs
and helped your Mama and I.

827
00:34:43,152 --> 00:34:44,661
We’ll never forget that.

828
00:34:44,686 --> 00:34:45,975
Thank you so much.

829
00:34:46,937 --> 00:34:47,961
You’re welcome.

830
00:34:49,535 --> 00:34:50,957
- Love you!
- Love you too!

831
00:34:51,149 --> 00:34:52,465
Love you, Tash!
Love you, Andres!

832
00:34:52,598 --> 00:34:53,598
Love you too, Dad!

833
00:34:53,790 --> 00:34:54,790
I love you!

834
00:34:54,815 --> 00:34:56,318
I love you all!

835
00:34:59,038 --> 00:35:00,698
Awww! She’s blushing!

836
00:35:01,347 --> 00:35:02,905
Just scratch harder!

837
00:35:02,930 --> 00:35:04,980
Just scratch harder on the back.
Not there!

838
00:35:05,216 --> 00:35:07,117
- Where?
- Okay, here on the back! There!

839
00:35:07,313 --> 00:35:09,679
There! Stop right there!
That’s good!

840
00:35:09,843 --> 00:35:10,843
Lola Maxi!

841
00:35:11,427 --> 00:35:12,427
BFF!

842
00:35:12,583 --> 00:35:14,019
Why are you scratching that?

843
00:35:14,361 --> 00:35:17,482
Hey, it’s fine if she scratches me!
Do you think it’s free?

844
00:35:17,776 --> 00:35:19,315
Every scratch costs money!

845
00:35:20,067 --> 00:35:21,380
Huh?! Lola Maxi!

846
00:35:21,405 --> 00:35:23,418
Oh, so it costs money!

847
00:35:24,095 --> 00:35:26,911
Never mind! I’m good! I’m good!

848
00:35:30,441 --> 00:35:31,617
Who taught you that?!

849
00:35:33,461 --> 00:35:35,158
Let’s just say goodbye.

850
00:35:35,748 --> 00:35:36,748
Let’s just say goodbye!

851
00:35:37,140 --> 00:35:42,186
You’ve just watched another
episode of Da Pers Family.

852
00:35:42,549 --> 00:35:45,009
It’s been fun again, thank you so much!

853
00:35:45,201 --> 00:35:47,013
Always remember—

854
00:35:47,454 --> 00:35:53,307
in struggle and in happiness,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!

855
00:35:54,615 --> 00:35:56,075
See you next week!

856
00:35:56,193 --> 00:35:57,478
- Bye-bye!
- See you, guys!
